      "FacilityID": 1000032522,
      "SummaryText": "13 OCA. \n\n\n\nAs part of this facility's commitment to provide a safe work environment, GAM has implemented a number of management programs to enhance safety.  Pertinent PSM & RMP information is communicated to plant employees weekly to review plant safety, health and environmental issues.  General awareness HF training is given to all site employees.  Operators of HF systems and Contractor employees receive additional site-specific training.  Components of the HF systems are covered under a Mechanical Integrity program to assure that they operate safely and are physically sound.  Appropriate standard operating procedures (work instructions) are in place for start-up and shutdown of the processes, in both normal and emergency situations.  Information on the chemical, process technology, and equipment has been compiled. Changes to the process are reviewed under Management Of Change procedures.  Pre-startup safety reviews are conducted prior to the implementation of any process change.  Contractors receive extensive safety training prior to beginning work in the facility.  Competence of the contractor employees is assured as part of the contractor selection program.  Hot work and other safe work permit programs are in place in the facility.  Process hazard analyses are conducted to identify potential hazards and areas for improvement.  Any incidents are investigated to determine the root cause and to identify changes to prevent recurrence.  The Risk Management Program is outlined and discussed in a PSM/RMP program document in use at the facility.\n\n\n\nGAM demonstrates its commitment to public and worker safety by a continuing accident prevention program.  All incidents and near misses are investigated to identify root causes with corrective actions aimed to prevent future occurrences. In the event of an HF or other chemical release, GAM has in place an Emergency Response (ER) Plan, which is reviewed and updated whenever a significant change to a chemical system, including"
